<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="564" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d564">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Food Administrator’s File</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Special Representative of the Food
                                    Administration</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_TAE1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Taylor</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                    the Food Administrator</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HHC1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hoover</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-16">
                                        <hi rend="italic">November 16, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>… Policy established and accepted that exportable North American
                                wheat is limited to 132,000,000 bushels. Allies would prefer to have
                                this all within three months. Expect to import 2,000,000 tons each
                                Argentine and India. In the event of hiatus prior to Argentine
                                deliveries would it be possible to borrow from United States
                                1,000,000 tons wheat and replace later from the Argentine Republic?
                                Attempting to increase use of oatmeal. Wire definite figure on
                                exportable surplus of rye and barley fit for human consumption.
                                …</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_TAE1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Taylor</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>